                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17531205-19-victim182 t17531205-19-viclabel92"></join>, who was in a coach, and I standing by the side. I felt a hand in my pocket, and turning saw the prisoner take my silk handkerchief from my right pocket. I ran after him, and took him; there were two others with him, and I believe he gave it to one of them. He was never out of my sight till taken. I searched him, but did not find my handkerchief.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I was coming along the strand, and neither touch'd or saw his handkerchief.</p>
